Portugal May Raise Minimum Early Retirement Age, Negocios Says

-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 
2011-10-12T06:57:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-12/portugal-may-raise-minimum-early-retirement-age-negocios-says.html
The  Portuguese government  may raise
the minimum age for voluntary early retirment to 57 from 55,
Jornal de Negocios reported, citing a preliminary proposal being
discussed as part of the 2012 budget.  Workers must also have contributed to social security for
at least 32 years, the Portuguese newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
